
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeStyle rectangle

class Song {
  -title: String
  -year: int
  -length: int
  -genre: String
  -artist: Artist
}

class Artist {
  -name: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
  -websiteURL: String
  +getArtistName(): String
}

class User {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -address: String
  +getId(): int
  +getName(): String
  +getAddress(): String
}

class RegularUser {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -address: String
  +buySingle(Song): void
  +createAlbum(Hit[]): Album
}

class BusinessUser {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -address: String
  -vatNumber: String
  +uploadSong(Song): void
}

class Hit {
  -song: Song
  -trackNumber: int
  -album: Album
}

class Album {
  -hits: Hit[]
  -suggestedTo: RegularUser[]
}

' Relationships

User <|-- RegularUser
User <|-- BusinessUser

Song "1" -- "1" Artist : belongs to
RegularUser "1" -- "1" Album : creates
BusinessUser "1" -- "1" Song : uploads
Song "1" -- "1" Hit : is a single
Hit "1" -- "1" Album : is part of
Album "1" -- "1" RegularUser : suggested to

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **Song** has a **one-to-one** relationship with **Artist** (a song belongs to exactly one artist).
- **User** is an abstract class from which **RegularUser** and **BusinessUser** inherit.
- **RegularUser** can **buy singles** and **create albums**.
- **BusinessUser** can **upload songs**.
- **Hit** is a type of **Song** (single), and it is part of an **Album**.
- An **Album** can be **suggested to** multiple **RegularUsers**.

